   3.806407953455371*^9, 3.8064080007534657`*^9}, {3.8064084606824207`*^9, 
   3.806408461502884*^9}, 3.806413380024214*^9, {3.80735380925058*^9, 
   3.807353810914628*^9}, {3.807354484033061*^9, 3.807354621821592*^9}, {
   3.807354693243346*^9, 3.807354697322055*^9}, {3.807354731458112*^9, 
   3.807354779309722*^9}, {3.8394272955586033`*^9, 3.839427297173159*^9}, {
   3.8394273337678685`*^9, 
   3.8394273355802355`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"a98dc03b-05db-4a5d-8ec4-\
d5b39fee73bc"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"E", "=", 
  StyleBox[
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["h",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], "\[Nu]"}]]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.839603643368307*^9, 
  3.8396036459660683`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"f41acfad-f658-4c65-bdc9-\
2b147c0ad3d2"],

Cell["\<\
which we now know as photons. He then proposed that the kinetic energy (KE ) \
of the emitted electrons is given by\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9338595221979218`*^9, 
  3.9338595296240864`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"f7dce8ed-28be-7343-ad60-\
40b684c338fc"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  StyleBox["KE",
   FontSlant->"Italic"], 
  StyleBox[" ",
   FontSlant->"Plain"], 
  StyleBox["=",
   FontSlant->"Plain"], 
  StyleBox[" ",
   FontSlant->"Plain"], 
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox[
    RowBox[{
     StyleBox["h",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], "\[Nu]"}]], "\[Minus]", 
   "\[Phi]"}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8394273548622656`*^9, 
  3.839427401831063*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"58426d31-7e85-432d-a60b-\
52ae0f763da3"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "where ",
 StyleBox["\[CapitalPhi]",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "  is the work function of the metal (the minimum energy required to release \
an electron from that metal). This equation shows how the electron kinetic \
energy is dependent on the light frequency. In addition, each photon can \
eject only one electron, so increasing light intensity increases the number \
of emitted electrons. The combined experiment and theory demonstrated the \
quantization of light."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.933859538781885*^9, 
  3.933859543518936*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"478e25ce-9a1e-484b-9929-\
ccc295d50e71"],

Cell["\<\
Einstein also predicted (to explain the photoelectric effect) that photons \
have momentum p,\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.9339511546936836`*^9},ExpressionUUID->"ccdd90ca-4f1c-ec4a-86e8-\
677d281cca2d"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  StyleBox["p",
   FontSlant->"Italic"], " ", 
  StyleBox["=",
   FontSlant->"Plain"], 
  StyleBox[" ",
   FontSlant->"Plain"], 
  FractionBox[
   StyleBox["h",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], "\[Lambda]"]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8394274858649683`*^9, 
  3.839427565827911*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"53099030-e7f7-7b43-ae42-\
d25491d1af09"],

Cell["\<\
where \[Lambda] is the wavelength of the light. How can a massless particle \
have momentum? That\[CloseCurlyQuote]s something we won\[CloseCurlyQuote]t \
discuss in this course, but it comes from using  relativity to describe the \
energy of the photon,\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.9338595676838875`*^9},ExpressionUUID->"cbadc899-42ed-8847-a575-\
7e8ec9f32abf"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  SuperscriptBox[
   StyleBox["E",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], "2"], " ", 
  StyleBox["=",
   FontSlant->"Plain"], 
  StyleBox[" ",
   FontSlant->"Plain"], 
  RowBox[{
   SuperscriptBox[
    RowBox[{
     StyleBox["(",
      FontSlant->"Plain"], 
     StyleBox["pc",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     StyleBox[")",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]}], "2"], "+", 
   SuperscriptBox[
    RowBox[{"(", 
     SuperscriptBox[
      StyleBox["mc",
       FontSlant->"Italic"], "2"], 
     StyleBox[")",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]}], "2"]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8394274858649683`*^9, 3.839427565827911*^9}, {
  3.914237685343977*^9, 3.914237729812066*^9}, {3.914237802084272*^9, 
  3.914237819214003*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"74fd8f13-dd28-a04f-87dd-\
b11853db7b61"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["de Broglie Waves", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8073548454666176`*^9, 3.807354871848152*^9}, {
  3.8073549209211054`*^9, 
  3.807354931229952*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"3c5fe721-9908-456f-b119-\
e5482ed94934"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["de Broglie\[CloseCurlyQuote]s Proposal", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.807355257800974*^9, 
  3.80735527407062*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"ccab41ed-3e2b-4271-9965-\
d2523e37562c"],

Cell["\<\
de Broglie had the idea to use Einstein\[CloseCurlyQuote]s light proposal \
(light was a wave that existed in quantized units) in reverse for matter \
(matter exists in quantized units that are also a wave). He proposed that for \
matter, just as for light,\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.807355304126342*^9, 3.807355390317481*^9}, {
  3.807355491683648*^9, 3.807355565030328*^9}, {3.8073556229204903`*^9, 
  3.807355730058307*^9}, {3.807355771513384*^9, 3.8073557761421604`*^9}, {
  3.807355806862008*^9, 3.8073558375342445`*^9}, {3.8073700905480447`*^9, 
  3.8073701758881683`*^9}, {3.8394280957437067`*^9, 3.839428109186911*^9}, {
  3.839603812671139*^9, 
  3.8396038133678246`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"df761da4-3fcd-49da-844c-\
671669f2b1df"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  StyleBox["p",
   FontSlant->"Italic"], " ", 
  StyleBox["=",
   FontSlant->"Plain"], 
  StyleBox[" ",
   FontSlant->"Plain"], 
  FractionBox[
   StyleBox["h",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], "\[Lambda]"]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8394274858649683`*^9, 
  3.839427565827911*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"34b0ddda-e6a9-465c-b69c-\
6e50514a2098"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "where \[Lambda] is the de Broglie wavelength. We are more familiar with \
this equation when we use ",
 StyleBox["p",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " = ",
 StyleBox["mv",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "  and rearrange to give"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.9339512220708313`*^9},ExpressionUUID->"a5cc8f30-ef8f-c84f-a18c-\
07f179d451ff"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"\[Lambda]", "=", 
  FractionBox[
   StyleBox["h",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   StyleBox["mv",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8394281351037655`*^9, 
  3.8394281423338675`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"c8906593-d014-4072-948d-\
14b61f37aca6"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "where ",
 StyleBox["m",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " is the particle mass and ",
 StyleBox["v",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " is the particle velocity."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.9339512924741592`*^9},ExpressionUUID->"d9655221-4be4-5845-a4e1-\
d2c5f08b2829"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Experimental Observation", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8073694623082542`*^9, 
  3.8073694723535357`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"e2c57a17-f5a3-4a32-ba96-\
c599b7ad83b7"],

Cell[TextData[StyleBox["Davisson and Germer observed diffraction of electrons \
from a Nickel surface, thus confirming experimentally de Broglie\
\[CloseCurlyQuote]s proposal. Their experimental setup is shown in Figure \
1.5.", "Text"]], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.807370006210079*^9, {3.9142379804342403`*^9, 
   3.9142379913255014`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"6d9fdf9b-fffb-4bc0-a105-\
1c1274d29dc3"],

