Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["The Heisenberg Uncertainty Principle", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.807624864656*^9, 
  3.807624872004979*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"3ba0f16a-1a52-448c-a159-\
cbe4c9633075"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Statement of the Principle", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.807624887420559*^9, 3.807624893194415*^9}, {
  3.807625032542676*^9, 
  3.807625033879361*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"6f06bdc4-875c-4222-8d5a-\
ce9e512c5a58"],

Cell["\<\
The idea we\[CloseCurlyQuote]ve been discussing, that the position \
distribution widens when the momentum distribution gets narrower, is in fact \
the basic idea of the Heisenberg Uncertainty Principle! More specifically, \
the principle states\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.807624896503544*^9, 
  3.8076249679658566`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"1abc6183-8856-433b-93e6-\
b34fd7952763"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  StyleBox[
   RowBox[{"\[CapitalDelta]", 
    StyleBox["x",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], "\[CapitalDelta]", 
    StyleBox["p",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]}]], "\[GreaterEqual]", 
  FractionBox["\[HBar]", "2"]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.807624977916951*^9, 
  3.8076250410256267`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"56302cc6-fbca-4c30-ac31-\
1adad9df73bb"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "that is, the uncertainty in the position (\[CapitalDelta]",
 StyleBox["x",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ") times the uncertainty in the momentum (\[CapitalDelta]",
 StyleBox["p",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ") cannot be smaller than a constant (\[HBar]/2). Calculating that constant \
as \[HBar]/2 is a bit more involved, and we won\[CloseCurlyQuote]t go through \
that right now. What\[CloseCurlyQuote]s important now is that you see how \
position and momentum are inherently related, and you can\[CloseCurlyQuote]t \
know both at the same time with infinite precision."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.807625069380132*^9, 
  3.807625271842272*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"62c5d521-29eb-4c84-808b-\
f6154e05607d"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["What is the Uncertainty?", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8076256830795507`*^9, 
  3.807625690045279*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"81fa1223-8a76-46f5-b3d3-\
f1d49d28f569"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "In introductory chemistry, the uncertainty in eq. 30 is just explained as \
the accuracy with which you can measure something. However, the formal \
definition of \[CapitalDelta]",
 StyleBox["x",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " or \[CapitalDelta]",
 StyleBox["p",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " above is the standard deviation of the distribution. Perhaps you\
\[CloseCurlyQuote]ve heard about standard deviation in a statistics or \
analytical chemistry course. If not, it is often represented by \[Sigma], and \
(loosely speaking) it is given by"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.807625695769491*^9, 3.807625712459958*^9}, {
  3.8076257854960375`*^9, 3.8076258889120193`*^9}, {3.8076259764430227`*^9, 
  3.8076260101080155`*^9}, {3.914239563510135*^9, 3.914239565578512*^9}, {
  3.9145996802740936`*^9, 3.9145996813142943`*^9}, {3.9340260011020393`*^9, 
  3.934026001975939*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"0b7fa7a1-76a6-4c9e-8f07-\
5afe6eeb41cf"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  SuperscriptBox["\[Sigma]", "2"], "=", 
  FractionBox[
   RowBox[{"\[Sum]", 
    SuperscriptBox[
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{
       StyleBox["x",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "-", 
       OverscriptBox[
        StyleBox["x",
         FontSlant->"Italic"], "_"]}], ")"}], "2"]}], 
   StyleBox["n",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8076260180185432`*^9, 3.8076260275804996`*^9}, {
  3.80762621722173*^9, 3.807626291891366*^9}, {3.807626327733724*^9, 
  3.807626333978409*^9}, {3.8076265195713887`*^9, 
  3.8076265198591576`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"69ac1acd-09a8-4ede-a368-\
40e9a18fa833"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "or the square of the standard deviation is equal to the square of the sum \
over the variation of each point from the mean value (",
 Cell[BoxData[
  OverscriptBox[
   StyleBox["x",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], "_"]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.8076260180185432`*^9, 3.8076260275804996`*^9}, {
   3.80762621722173*^9, 3.807626291891366*^9}, {3.807626327733724*^9, 
   3.807626333978409*^9}},ExpressionUUID->
  "1f233c48-4671-4779-81bf-516704ebc093"],
 ") divided by the number of points. It\[CloseCurlyQuote]s a measure of how \
far your points are from the average. \n\nIf we know a bit more about our \
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]wave\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote], then we can in fact \
calculate the standard deviation, but for now, this just gives you a general \
idea of what the uncertainty actually refers to."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.807626390049427*^9, 3.807626493091502*^9}, {
  3.8076265347201767`*^9, 
  3.8076265964465494`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"10f068a8-771c-4887-bcb4-\
09ec70a6d87f"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Looking Ahead", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.807626741983536*^9, 
  3.80762674463137*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"9419c60c-90bf-48f7-9fdc-\
eb4a13a2dd31"],

Cell["\<\
Up to this point, we\[CloseCurlyQuote]ve talked a lot about \
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]waves\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] in the most vague sense. \
\>", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8076267479619064`*^9, 
  3.807626953973007*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"6f207f1d-5e3c-4af0-b23f-\
59d6a9ed94f8"],

Cell["\<\
We said that de Broglie proposed particles have some wavelength given by an \
equation. \
\>", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8076267479619064`*^9, 
  3.807626956906344*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"5b08cfe9-943e-4cad-a1bc-\
dda0b405044a"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "We then plugged this into the Fourier transform formula to convert from \
wavelength (\[Lambda]) to angular frequency (\[Omega]) to momentum (",
 StyleBox["p",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "). "
}], "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8076267479619064`*^9, 
  3.8076269602840815`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"13821369-dd48-428f-9e0d-\
c80a958f6073"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "But we haven't said anything about the nature of this wave. Indeed, we \
haven't said what the ",
 StyleBox["wavefunction",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " (the function related to a particle wave) looks like. "
}], "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8076267479619064`*^9, 
  3.80762696504856*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"d89d01f0-2c41-48f5-8820-\
07b537818849"],

Cell["\<\
That's what Schr\[ODoubleDot]dinger (and Heisenberg) discovered, and we\
\[CloseCurlyQuote]ll be discussing it in the coming lessons\
\>", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8076267479619064`*^9, 3.8076269405683856`*^9}, {
  3.8076269981909466`*^9, 
  3.8076270352568693`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"2579f74e-803b-497d-8664-\
56710df27d6f"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]]
},
